Looks like he was hosting a sick pregame. At least it sounded pretty chill from how @haileesteinfeld described it. A bunch of phone towers in our area got knocked down recently so our service has been spotty. Probably why Dooley’s invited didn’t get through to us. No hard feelings. Can’t believe we missed out on Jason Derulo, though. That stings a little.

Also, big shoutout to @skyler.fulton who directed this bad boy. And who is, by all measures, our absolute boy. We’ll get to Dooley eventually. This is our promise.

Love, 
Jack, Max, Sam (and Intern Pierre) 🤝

node.text: @welcometofriday.pod drops tomorrow. This is the biggest thing we’ve worked on for Friday Beers and is the start of a huge new next chapter where we’ll be unleashing a lot of new content. Tons of great actors and comics helped us make it, along with the folks at @allthingscomedy 🤝 Big thanks to @almadrigal @mbertolina and @wilfredburr (he’s got no idea who we are, but still). Dial this thing up before you commence suckdown tomorrow, we could not be more hyped for you to hear it. Link in bio, as always. Enjoy.

node.text: Tomorrow is important for a couple reasons. It’s Friday, but it’s also the launch of our sketch comedy show @welcometofriday.pod on all major streaming platforms. We’re not proud of much. But we’re really proud of this show. We think it’s funny and we think you will think it’s funny too. So much so, that if you listen and don’t think it’s funny, you can tell us directly (@jbfresh2 and @maxwellredington). That’s right. We’re putting our personal instas on the line. That’s how confident we are in this show. Or maybe how delusional we are. There’s really only one way to find out. By listening to @welcometofriday.pod first episode when it drops tomorrow. Link in bio to subscribe. Happy Almost Friday, love you - Jack and Max
